I prefer using digital books because I can basically "control-f" and I prefer taking notes on it (whereas for physical books I have to be careful with markups since I sell the books after).  As for taking notes, I prefer handwritten or using an Apple Pencil over typing.  There are a lot of medical students that actually use the iPad with the pencil to take notes. Plus, if you are given ppt. slides you can write directly on them and follow along in class.
